msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:3
msgid "1. Purpose"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:5
msgid ""
"Mission: The Carpentries builds global capacity in essential data and "
"computational skills for conducting efficient, open, and reproducible "
"research. We train and foster an active, inclusive, diverse community of "
"learners and instructors that promotes and models the importance of "
"software and data in research. We collaboratively develop openly-"
"available lessons and deliver these lessons using evidence-based teaching"
" practices. We focus on people conducting and supporting research."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:7
msgid "2. Lesson Program Membership"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:9
#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:90
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:10
msgid ""
"Lesson Programs are collections of lessons which comprise one or more "
"Carpentries workshops and the leadership guiding their development and "
"implementation. The following requirements outline the general "
"expectations associated with Lesson Programs; additional detail can be "
"found in the Lesson Program Policy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:12
msgid "Eligibility for Lesson Program Membership"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:13
msgid ""
"The Executive Council is responsible for assessing a prospective Lesson "
"Program for acceptance into The Carpentries, which requires a majority "
"vote. The Executive Director will be responsible for developing and "
"implementing policies related to Lesson Program incubation and assessing "
"the ability of the staff and community to meet obligations associated "
"with new Lesson Programs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:15
msgid "Roles and Responsibilities of Lesson Programs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:16
msgid ""
"A Lesson Program within The Carpentries should possess the following "
"characteristics:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:17
msgid ""
"Intention and purpose for lessons that align with The Carpentries mission"
" and vision"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:18
msgid ""
"Goals and objectives for lessons and/or workshops that are distinct from "
"other Lesson Programs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:19
msgid "Service to a particular audience of learners and instructors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:20
msgid ""
"Evidence of community member commitment to Lesson Program governance (see"
" below), lesson maintenance, and curriculum development"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:22
msgid "Governance of Lesson Programs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:23
msgid ""
"Each Lesson Program will have a Lesson Program Committee to serve as "
"community governance organization and act as a point of contact with The "
"Carpentries Executive Council and staff. The Lesson Program Committee "
"will provide the Executive Council with an annual report of Lesson "
"Program operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:25
msgid "Resignation and Termination of Lesson Programs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:26
msgid ""
"In the event that either the Lesson Program or The Carpentries is not "
"fulfilling its obligations under the Lesson Program Policy, or the "
"mission and vision of The Carpentries and the Lesson Program no longer "
"align, the relationship between the Lesson Program and the Carpentries "
"can be terminated. The Executive Council may decide to retire the Lesson "
"Program through a majority vote, or the Lesson Program Committee can "
"choose to discontinue the Lesson Program's association with the "
"Carpentries. In either case, notice must be given to the other "
"organization to arrange for separation of responsibilities and resources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:28
msgid "3. Organizational Membership"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:29
msgid "Eligibility, Rights, and Termination of Organizational Members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:30
msgid ""
"Member Organizations have committed to supporting the maintenance and "
"growth of the Carpentries community according to the specific details "
"outlined in each institution's Membership Agreement. In general, Member "
"Organizations financially support The Carpentries in exchange for "
"priority access to instructor training and guidance in building training "
"capacity at their organization."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:32
msgid "4. Individual Voting Membership"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:34
msgid ""
"The Carpentries community includes many opportunities for involvement "
"representing variable levels of commitment. All individuals participating"
" in community activities are required to conform to the Code of Conduct. "
"Individuals may choose to commit to serving in one or more formal roles "
"in the community, such as instructor, trainer, or maintainer, as defined "
"by The Carpentries Handbook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:36
msgid "Eligibility, Rights, and Termination for Voting Members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:37
msgid ""
"Individuals who satisfy at least one of the following conditions are "
"eligible for Voting Membership, as assessed in a yearly timeframe "
"associated with the dates of the election (Dec 1 to Nov 30):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:39
msgid ""
"Every individual who has completed instructor or trainer certification in"
" the past year"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:40
msgid ""
"Every individual who has completed their instructor certification in the "
"last two years and has taught at least one workshop of The Carpentries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:41
msgid ""
"Every individual who is a certified instructor and has taught at least "
"two workshops of The Carpentries in the past two years"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:42
msgid ""
"Any individual who has participated on a committee, served as a mentor or"
" maintainer, or otherwise made a significant contribution, to any Lesson "
"Program or The Carpentries organization in the past year, as determined "
"on a case-by-case basis by the Executive Council, and thus is considered "
"active in the community"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:44
msgid "The Executive Director is not eligible for Voting Membership."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:46
msgid ""
"All individuals who satisfy conditions for 1-3 above are automatically "
"tracked and will receive Voting Membership. Any individual who only "
"satisfies condition 4 may receive Voting Membership by contacting The "
"Carpentries staff within a reasonable timeframe prior to release of "
"ballots to confirm their participation, as dictated by the Election "
"Policy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:48
msgid ""
"Any individual who no longer wishes to be affiliated with The Carpentries"
" or included as a Voting Member must inform The Carpentries staff for "
"removal from membership lists. Voting Membership may be terminated by a "
"majority vote of the Executive Council for individuals who are "
"recommended for termination by the Code of Conduct committee or Executive"
" Director for non-compliance with The Carpentries policies or violation "
"of the core values of The Carpentries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:50
msgid "5. Executive Council"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:52
msgid "General Powers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:53
msgid ""
"As the highest leadership body of the organization, the Executive Council"
" is responsible for:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:54
msgid "determining the mission and purposes of the organization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:55
msgid "selecting the Executive Director and evaluating their performance"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:56
msgid "strategic and organizational planning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:57
msgid "ensuring strong fiduciary oversight and financial management"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:58
msgid "identifying revenue streams and resource development"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:59
msgid "approving and monitoring The Carpentries programs and services"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:60
msgid "enhancing The Carpentries public image"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:61
msgid "assessing its own performance as the governing body of The Carpentries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:63
msgid "Responsibilities of Executive Council Members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:64
msgid "Each Member of the Executive Council is responsible for:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:65
msgid "knowing the organization’s mission, policies, programs, and needs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:66
msgid "reading and understanding the organization’s financial statements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:67
msgid ""
"serving as active advocates and ambassadors for the organization "
"necessary for The Carpentries to advance its mission"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:68
msgid ""
"leveraging connections, networks, and resources to develop collective "
"action to fully achieve the Carpentries’ mission"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:69
msgid ""
"helping identify personal connections that can benefit the organization’s"
" fundraising and reputational standing, and can influence public policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:70
msgid ""
"preparing for, attending, and conscientiously participating in Executive "
"Council meetings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:72
msgid "Number, Tenure, Requirements, and Qualifications"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:73
msgid ""
"The Executive Council will be composed of nine (9) Members, each serving "
"a two-year term, without limit on the number of terms. Member terms will "
"begin on February 1st, except when filling between-election vacancies "
"(see below). Five (5) Members of the Executive Council will be elected by"
" the Executive Council (hereafter referred to as \"Council-elected "
"Members\"). The other four (4) Members will be elected by the Membership "
"of the organization (\"Community-elected Members\"). No employer may have"
" more than two elected or appointed representatives on the Executive "
"Council, and Carpentries staff are not eligible to serve as Executive "
"Council Members. The Executive Council has the final say in determining "
"whether people are working for the same employer. If more than two people"
" who are working for the same employer are elected, they must step down "
"one by one to be replaced by other nominees in order of the number of "
"votes received."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:76
msgid "Regular Meetings and Quorum"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:77
msgid ""
"The Executive Council must meet at least ten (10) times per year, either "
"in person or online. Quorum for meetings of the Executive Council is five"
" Members, including at least one Council-elected and one Community-"
"elected Member."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:79
msgid "Compensation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:80
msgid ""
"Members of the Executive Council shall not receive compensation from the "
"Organization for their service, with the exception of administrative "
"support, travel, and accommodation costs related to their duties on the "
"Executive Council."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:82
msgid "Confidentiality"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:83
msgid ""
"Members of the Executive Council will sometimes discuss or be made aware "
"of information or activities that may be sensitive to share publicly "
"(e.g. salary information). Executive Council Members are expected to "
"treat such information confidentially and to disclose such information to"
" those outside the Executive Council only when the Executive Council has "
"agreed that such dissemination is appropriate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:85
msgid "Removal"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:86
msgid ""
"If a Member of the Executive Council consistently fails to meet the "
"obligations outlined above, they may be removed by a vote of three-"
"quarters (3/4) of the other Members of the Executive Council. A vote to "
"remove a Member must be announced in writing to the entire Executive "
"Council at least ten (10) days in advance of the vote. A vacated "
"Executive Council seat will be filled following the Between-election "
"vacancies procedure outlined in the Nominations and Elections section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:88
msgid "6. Nominations and Elections"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:91
msgid ""
"Four (4) to five (5) of the nine (9) Members of the Executive Council "
"will be elected each year, either by the community (Community-elected) or"
" by the Executive Council (Council-elected). A general timeline for "
"elections will occur annually as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:92
msgid ""
"Mid-October: Executive Council announces election, soliciting self-"
"nominations for Community-elected Members and recommendations for "
"Council-elected Members, and identifying areas of expertise desired by "
"the Council"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:93
msgid ""
"Late November: Self-nominations and recommendations close and the "
"Executive Council hosts Community Calls to discuss the election and "
"introduce candidates for Community-elected Members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:94
msgid "Early December: Voting Members vote for Community-elected Members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:95
msgid ""
"Mid-December: Executive Council elects Council-elected Members and "
"announces the Executive Council Members for the following year"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:96
msgid ""
"February 1: Responsibility for governance is transferred to the new "
"Executive Council"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:98
msgid "Community-elected Members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:99
msgid ""
"Two (2) Community-elected Members will be elected each year by the Voting"
" Members of The Carpentries. Any Voting Member of The Carpentries may "
"stand for election by announcing their candidacy as dictated by the "
"Election Policy; Carpentries staff may not stand for election. If there "
"are fewer than two candidates for the election, the current Community-"
"elected Members will decide amongst them who will remain in office."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:101
msgid ""
"Elections will take place once every calendar year and no later than 30 "
"days before the new Executive Council becomes active (February 1). Each "
"Voting Member may vote for as many candidates as there are Community-"
"elected Member seats to be filled. The candidates who receive the highest"
" number of votes will be elected into the Executive Council."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:103
msgid "Council-elected Members"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:104
msgid ""
"Two (2) or three (3) of the Council-elected Members will be elected each "
"year. The Executive Council must consider at least one more candidate "
"than the number of Council-elected Member seats to be filled. Anyone may "
"recommend candidates for Council-elected positions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:106
msgid ""
"Executive Council selects, by anonymous vote, the Council-elected Members"
" from among the recommended candidates. Appointed Members will abstain "
"from voting when they themselves are recommended for reappointment. Each "
"Executive Council Member may vote for as many individuals as there are "
"Council-elected Member seats to be filled. The individuals with the "
"highest number of votes will be appointed. This vote will not take place "
"until after the voting results for Community-elected Members are known "
"and no later than December 15th."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:108
msgid "Between-election vacancies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:109
msgid ""
"If an Executive Council seat of a Community-elected Member becomes vacant"
" after the beginning of the year but before the first of October, the "
"Executive Council will strive to fill the seat with one of the non-"
"elected nominees from the previous year’s election, in the order of the "
"number of votes they received. If this effort fails, the Executive "
"Council may appoint a Voting Member to fill the seat."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:111
msgid ""
"If an Executive Council seat of a Council-elected Member becomes vacant "
"after the beginning of the year but before the first of October, the "
"Executive Council will strive to fill the seat with another eligible "
"Voting Member."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:113
msgid ""
"In both of these cases, the vacancy will be filled by the new Executive "
"Council Member for the remainder of the original term only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/governance/bylaws.md:115
msgid "7. Officers"
msgstr ""

